         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. Z. explains the ḳeriat shemah based on the
                            commentary on S. Otiyot. One problem of kavvanot, even from the Zohar,
                            is that they are not equally applicable to all souls. He criticizes
                            Nathan Shapira for mixing derushim with kavvanot, but drew knowledge
                            about kavvanot from the derushiim for his own Sefer ha-Kavvanot. Z.
                            praises his students Benjamin ha-Kohen and Abraham Rovigo who copied
                            kavvanot. He has especially high hopes for Benjamin ha-Kohen to whom he
                            gave all the texts that he did not possess before. In his first
                            introduction Zohar Ḥadash, he already explained correspondence of the
                            letters in the Torah to essences in the supernal lights (orot
                            eliyionim). The other two introductions are excerpts from Ḥayyim Vital.
                            Bedeutung von S. Otiyot, Shema-Lesung auf dem Bett, Zoharinterpretation,
                            Entsprechung der Buchstaben in der Torah zu spez. Essenzen in den Orot
                            Eliyonim</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">נפשי השלמה עמ״ו נהמ״ה</note>
         </notesStmt>
